Egypt Military Sets Up Constitution Advisory Committee, WSJ Says

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-02-15T23:07:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/egypt-military-sets-up-constitution-advisory-committee-wsj-says.html
  Egypt ’s military set up a committee
of eight people to suggest changes to the nation’s constitution,
the Wall Street Journal reported.   The committee is tasked with revising six articles of the
constitution and was requested to issue recommendations within
10 days, the WSJ said.   Seperately, Ghad Party-head Ayman Nour became the first to
declare his candidacy for president, according to the report.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:
